riorates%3F%20If%20you%20make%20a%20poor%20investment%20decision%20that%20costs%20you%3F%20If%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20simply%20exceeds%20what%20you%20planned%20to%20spend%20annually%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20our%20clients%20want%20to%20retire%20early%2C%20we%20support%20that%20choice%20%E2%80%94%20and%20we%20want%20to%20build%20a%20%3Cem%3Erealistic%3C%2Fem%3E%20plan%20for%20doing%20so.%20That%20means%20we%20don't%20assume%20they'll%20be%20able%20to%20spend%20half%20of%20what%20they%20do%20now%20once%20they%20retire%20or%20that%20their%20current%20lifestyle%20is%20the%20one%20they'll%20%3Cem%3Ealways%3C%2Fem%3E%20be%20happy%20with%20for%20all%20eternity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20are%20not%20the%20same%20person%20you%20were%20five%20years%20ago%2C%20and%20it's%20very%20unlikely%20you%20will%20be%20the%20same%20person%20as%20you%20are%20today%20in%2010%2C%2015%2C%20or%2020%20years.%20Don't%20lock%20yourself%20into%20lifestyle%20choices%20now%20that%20you%20may%20find%20unsatisfactory%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESave%20a%20very%20large%20percentage%20of%20your%20income%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20how%20do%20you%20build%20financial%20power%20to%20support%20a%20plan%20that%20allows%20you%20to%20retire%20early%20without%20limiting%20yourself%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20contribute%20a%20%3Cem%3Esignificant%20%3C%2Fem%3Eamount%20of%20your%20current%20annual%20income%20to%20long-term%20investments%20to%20grow%20wealth%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20significant%2C%20we're%20talking%20about%20saving%20a%20minimum%20of%2030%25%20of%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-adjusted-gross-income-agi-taxes%5C%22%3Egross%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERealistically%2C%20that%20figure%20likely%20needs%20to%20be%20closer%20to%2040%25%20or%20even%2050%25%20if%20you%20want%20to%20retire%20in%20your%2040s%20or%2050s.%20(Remember%2C%20the%20%26quot%3Bnormal%26quot%3B%20retirement%20age%20is%2067%2C%20so%